'''''Don't Be Afraid of the Dark''''' is a 2010 [[horror film]] written by [[Matthew Robbins (screenwriter)|Matthew Robbins]] and [[Guillermo Del Toro]] as a remake of the 1973 [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] [[television movie|made-for-television]] [[horror film]] [[Don't Be Afraid of the Dark (1973 film)|of the same name]].<ref name="V1">{{cite news|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118003272.html?categoryid=13&cs=1|title='Dark' days for Katie Holmes|last=Fleming|first=Michael|date=May 6, 2009|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=2009-08-18}}</ref>  The film stars [[Katie Holmes]], [[Guy Pearce]], and [[Bailee Madison]], and is being directed by first time director and [[Guillermo del Toro|del Toro]] protege [[Troy Nixey]].<ref name="V1"/><ref name="R1">{{cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/filmNews/idUSN3040459320080730|title=Del Toro and Miramax not "Afraid of the Dark"|last=Goldstein|first=Greg|date=July 30, 2008|publisher=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=2009-08-18}}</ref><ref name="R2">{{cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/filmNews/idUSTRE55T0RH20090630|title=Pearce, Madison not afraid of "Dark"|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=June 30, 2009|publisher=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=2009-08-18}}</ref>

==Production==
Filming began in July 2009 in [[Melbourne, Australia]], and went into post-production in September.<ref name="FS1">{{cite web|url=http://www.firstshowing.net/2009/08/03/troy-nixey-playing-with-simple-machines-after-del-toros-dark/|title=Troy Nixey Playing with 'Simple Machines' After Del Toro's Dark|last=Billington|first=Alex|date=August 3, 2009|publisher=First Showing|accessdate=2009-08-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sawfnews.com/Gossip/58992.aspx|title=Katie Holmes and Suri Cruise soak the Oz sun |date=July 22, 2009|publisher=SAWF News|accessdate=2009-08-18}}</ref>

==Plot==
A young girl, ([[Bailee Madison |Madison]]) after moving in with her father ([[Guy Pearce |Pearce]]) and his girlfriend ([[Katie Holmes |Holmes]]) soon discovers creatures are living in the house with them. Originally thought to be friendly, she soon learns otherwise.

